parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear differential can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: Whining
growling
or howling noise from the rear differential
vibration
and loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: Loss of power
inability to shift gears
transmission fluid leaks
and unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle seal can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. It can also lead to costly repairs and downtime.
symptoms: Leaking axle seal
loss of power
and unusual noises.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the dashboard goes black
the anti-theft system warning message is displayed
and the vehicle fails to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The fuel gauge does not provide accurate readings
the fuel pump sending unit overheats
and there is a strong smell of gasoline leaking from the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The key fails to release from the ignition
the vehicle fails to start
and the ignition switch is difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake warning light illuminates
the brake fluid leaks into the computer
and the vehicle's brakes are difficult to use.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to provide timely and accurate recall notifications can lead to delays in repairing safety-critical issues.
symptoms: The recall notification is received late
the parts needed for the repair are unavailable
and the manufacturer provides misleading information.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent failure of the brakes can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when driving at low speeds.
symptoms: The brakes may fail to engage or may engage erratically
causing the vehicle to slow down or stop unexpectedly. The brake pedal may feel soft or spongy
and the vehicle may make a grinding or vibrating noise when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion of the brake lines can cause brake fluid leaks, leading to a loss of brake pressure and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
soft or spongy brake pedal
grinding or vibrating noise when the brakes are applied.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Soft or spongy brake pedal
grinding or vibrating noise when the brakes are applied
brake fluid leaks.
